			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How much CHA is enough?<a name="71176"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 16 04 7:22 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It depends largely on what you're doing.
<br />

<br />
CHA is used for three things:  
<br />

<br />
(1) Prices at a vendor.  I believe ~150 CHA is enough to get you the best prices anywhere.
<br />
(2) Lull fatal resists.  If a lulll is resisted, the higher your charisma, the greater the chance the mobs will simply ignore the lull attempt and not aggro.  Note that CHA does not help lull land in the first place.  It only matters when lull is resisted.  In my experience doing LDoN hard dungeons from levels 62 - 65, singing CHA song to get me from 240 to 290 charisma helped reduce critical lull failures.
<br />
(3) Divine Intervention.  The higher your CHA, the greater the chance that DI will fire.  Tanks subjectively report that going from 250 to 355 CHA made DI fire more often.  You could peruse the cleric forums if you really wanted to get the numbers on this one.
<br />

<br />
HP is certainly king because HP will help you in every setting.
<br />
AC helps if you're being hit.
<br />
INT helps your mana pool, which is very useful if you do a lot of charming or fading.
<br />

<br />
I hope that helps.
<br />

<br />
Calli</span></td>
