				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How much CHA is enough?<a name="71306"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 20 04 2:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My experience had me wanting the most charisma I could find during the mid bard years before massive aa's and the post 65 levels.  It was more key during those lull moments with a song that worked back in the day to split old content. (ldon, bot..)
<br />

<br />
Now I could care less about charisma...there is no more missed notes once you have the right aa's spent, there is no more lull really since it is no longer a functional song post nerf..and post nerfed upgrade (back of the songbook like so many other songs), and the new content does not lend itself to using lull much in our pulls.  Now we use fade combos much more.
<br />

<br />
If you are a 50ish to 65ish bard I think Charisma is important during that period of gameplay,  and right when it really does not matter anymore...your gear will have lots on it anyways due to the upgrades you've amassed.
<br />

<br />
Moose</span></td>
