			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Debunking the myths<a name="71365"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 21 04 1:27 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>DEX helping songs last their full duration is a myth.  If you're talking about regular group songs, reducing lag and increasing your instrument skills are the only things that will help them last longer.
<br />

<br />
CHA affecting missed notes is also a myth.  There are parses on tCH that prove it.  However, if you want to stop missing notes altogether, get Mastery of the Past.  Reducing lag and max-ing your instrument skills will also help you here.
<br />

<br />
CHA does not help mez or charm last longer or be resisted less.  There is a dev post in one of the Hall of Fames somewhere stating it.  To help mez or charm last longer, reduce the mob's magic resist.
<br />

<br />
Calli</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
